}


}



/*
In this implementation, we use the sibling selector ~ to target the ytd-rich-grid-renderer element that is a sibling of the #guide element. The [page-subtype="home"] attribute selector limits the style rules to only be applied on the home page.

-> This is the parent of everything and is the ONLY class that makes it work it's charm:  ytd-page-manager

When the #guide element is hovered over, the adjacent ytd-rich-grid-renderer element has its --ytd-rich-grid-items-per-row custom property set to 7 with the !important declaration to override any other conflicting styles.

When not hovering over the #guide element, the ytd-rich-grid-renderer element has --ytd-rich-grid-items-per-row set to 8.
*/
}

